# 2. Comparison Operators (Integer Comparisons)
These operators are used with if statements to compare integer values.

- Equal (``): Checks if two values are equal.

  if [ "$a" -eq "$b" ]; then
      echo "a is equal to b"
  fi


- Not Equal (`-ne`): Checks if two values are not equal.

  if [ "$a" -ne "$b" ]; then
      echo "a is not equal to b"
  fi


